315":"1315年","about 1280":"大約1280年","1350":"1350年","1250":"1250年","1280":"1280年","1328":"1328年","1317":"1317年","1290":"1290年","England":"英國","lifeSummary":"Alexander Pope是Thomas Pope的兒子，於大約1280年出生在英國。他至少有1個兒子。他去世於1350年享年71歲。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1280–1350":"大约1280年–1350年","1280–1350":"1280年–1350年","1305–Male":"1305年–殁","1250–Male":"1250年–殁","1305":"1305年","1315":"1315年","about 1280":"大约1280年","1350":"1350年","1250":"1250年","1280":"1280年","1328":"1328年","1317":"1317年","1290":"1290年","England":"英国","lifeSummary":"Alexander Pope是Thomas Pope的儿子，于大约1280年出生在英国。他至少有1个儿子。他去世于1350年享年71岁。"},"hr":{"about 1280–1350":"oko 1280.–1350.","1280–1350":"1280–1350.","1305–Male":"1305–preminuo","1250–Male":"1250–preminuo","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1280":"oko 1280.","1350":"1350.","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England"},"cs":{"about 1280–1350":"okolo 1280–1350","1280–1350":"1280–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Zesnulý","1250–Male":"1250–Zesnulý","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1280":"okolo 1280","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"Anglie"},"da":{"about 1280–1350":"omkring 1280–1350","1280–1350":"1280–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Afdød","1250–Male":"1250–Afdød","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1280":"omkring 1280","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England"},"nl":{"about 1280–1350":"circa 1280–1350","1280–1350":"1280–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Overleden","1250–Male":"1250–Overleden","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1280":"circa 1280","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England"},"en":{"about 1280–1350":"about 1280–1350","1280–1350":"1280–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Deceased","1250–Male":"1250–Deceased","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1280":"about 1280","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pope","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>pope</i> (derived via Old English from Late Latin <i>papa</i> ‘bishop, pope’, from Greek <i>pappas</i> ‘father’, in origin a nursery word.) In the early Christian Church, the Latin term was at first used as a title of respect for male clergy of every rank, but in the Western Church it gradually came to be restricted to bishops, and then only to the bishop of Rome; in the Eastern Church it continued to be used of all priests (see   Popov  ,   Papas  ). The nickname would have been used for a vain or pompous man, or for someone who had played the part of the pope in a pageant or play. The surname is also present in Ireland and Scotland.","North German: variant of   Poppe  .","German: translation of   Pabst  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Popov","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Russian Nikolay, Oleg, Grigoriy, Anatoly, Andrei, Arkadi, Dmitriy, Mikhail, Sergey.  Bulgarian or Macedonian Atanas, Dimitar, Yordan.  Serbian Bosko, Bozidar, Branko.","Russian, Bulgarian, Macedonian, Serbian, and Rusyn: patronymic from <i>pop</i> ‘priest’, from Greek <i>pappas</i> ‘father’ (compare English   Pope  ). The name may sometimes derive from a nickname, but celibacy was not enjoined on priests of the Orthodox Church and so the name can indeed mean ‘son of the priest’. In many cases, however, the Russian name means no more than ‘of the priest’ and designates a servant of a priest. Compare   Popoff  , see also   Pop   2,   Popovic  , and   Popovski   1.","Jewish (American): most likely a shortened form of   Popovski   2. Compare   Popoff  ."]},{"name":"Papke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Bernhard, Erwin, Hans, Otto, Willi.","North German (also <b>Päpke</b>): nickname from a diminutive of Low German <i>pape</i>, Dutch <i>paepe</i> ‘pope’. Compare   Pope  ."]}]},{"name":"Alexander","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin form of the Greek name <i>Alexandros</i>, from <i>alexein</i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":10,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705191,"age":35,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":48,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Alexander Pope was born about 1280, in England as the son of Thomas Pope. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1350, at the age of 71."},"et":{"about 1280–1350":"umbes 1280–1350","1280–1350":"1280–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about